ipAddress.name: ipAddress
ipAddress.description: IP address for the management port of this entity.

netMask.name: netMask
netMask.description: The netmask for the management port of this entity.

defaultGateway.name: defaultGateway
defaultGateway.description: The IP address of the Default Gateway for this entity.

broadcastAddress.name: broadcastAddress
broadcastAddress.description: The broadcast address for the management port of this entity.

maxMacAddresses.name: maxMacAddresses
maxMacAddresses.description: Largest aggregate number of MAC addresses which this entity can support simultaneously.

clearStatistics.name: clearStatistics
clearStatistics.description: Setting this variable to TRUE (1) clears the traffic statistics accumulators on this entity. Setting this variable to any other value has no effect. The variable always returns 0 when read.

ageFilterDatabase.name: ageFilterDatabase
ageFilterDatabase.description: Setting this variable to FALSE (0) causes this entity to stop aging out entries from its filter database. Setting this variable to TRUE (1) causes this entity to age out filter database entries as defined in IEEE 802.1D. Whenever this entity restarts, this variable keeps previously assigned value.

entMibVersion.name: entMibVersion
entMibVersion.description: The revision level of the MIB contained in the CP firmware.

telnetEnable.name: telnetEnable
telnetEnable.description: The current state of the telnet daemon in the Switch. If this field is set to disable, external accesses via telnet will not be permitted.

syslogEnable.name: syslogEnable
syslogEnable.description: The current state of remote IP system logging. If enabled, the Switch will log messages to the SyslogIp IP address. If it is disabled, it will log messages to the console only.

syslogIp.name: syslogIp
syslogIp.description: The Ip address for remote IP system logging. If syslogEnabled is enabled, the Switch log messages to this IP.

syslogCmds.name: syslogCmds
syslogCmds.description: If system logging is enabled, this field enables or disables the logging of commands issued on a terminal command line.

syslogOut.name: syslogOut
syslogOut.description: If system logging is enabled, this field enables or disables the logging of output from the terminal.

nvramLoadSave.name: nvramLoadSave
nvramLoadSave.description: This field triggers loading and saving of the system settings in non-volatile RAM space. To trigger a load or a save the NVRAM IP address must first be set below. This field is always read as one. The filename used will be the hexadecimal value of this systems IP address.

nvramLastOpStat.name: nvramLastOpStat
nvramLastOpStat.description: This field shows the outcome of the last NVRAM load or save. If the NVRAM update was sucessful, this field will return one.

nvramRemoteIp.name: nvramRemoteIp
nvramRemoteIp.description: This is the IP address of the remote tftp machine where the NVRAM is to be loaded or saved. For nvramLoadSave to have an effect, this field must be set to a vaild IP address.

nvramRemotePath.name: nvramRemotePath
nvramRemotePath.description: This is the path on the remote machine where the NVRAM image is to be retrieved or stored. This path does not include the filename, and does not end with a /. This field is optional, and if left empty, the system will use the default tftp location.

diagnosticsResults.name: diagnosticsResults
diagnosticsResults.description: A result of the most recent diagnostic test for the whole stack.

diagnosticsTime.name: diagnosticsTime
diagnosticsTime.description: The date and time of the most recent diagnostic test for the whole stack.

lastDiagnosticsTest.name: lastDiagnosticsTest
lastDiagnosticsTest.description: The number indicating what diagnostic test was run last. The list represents the power-up diagnostic test sequence. Normally the returned value should be the index of the last test in the sequence.

commNumComms.name: commNumComms
commNumComms.description: The number of SNMP Communities currently configured in this system. This number should reflect the number of entries in the commInfoTable.

commInfoTable.name: commInfoTable
commInfoTable.description: A list of Switch Configuration Community Entries

commInfoEntry.name: commInfoEntry
commInfoEntry.description: A list of Community properties for the Switch.

commInfoIndex.name: commInfoIndex
commInfoIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the Switch Community Info Table.

commInfoName.name: commInfoName
commInfoName.description: The name of this Switch Community Entry.

commInfoGet.name: commInfoGet
commInfoGet.description: The GET permission for the community.

commInfoSet.name: commInfoSet
commInfoSet.description: The SET permission for the community.

commInfoTrap.name: commInfoTrap
commInfoTrap.description: The TRAP permission for the community.

commAltTrapPort.name: commAltTrapPort
commAltTrapPort.description: An alternate port to which the agent will send TRAP notifications. Note that the agent will continue to send TRAPs to the SNMP port. Setting this value to zero disables sending TRAPs to the alternate port.

commSnmpSecurityLevel.name: commSnmpSecurityLevel
commSnmpSecurityLevel.description: Security level to be used by the agent when checking requests. Level 1 check community string on get and set. Level 2 check community string on get, community string and host on set Level 3 check community string and host on get and set.

hostNumHosts.name: hostNumHosts
hostNumHosts.description: The current number of SNMP hosts in the system. Each host is allowed to perform get, set, and trap operations based on its associated community.

hostInfoTable.name: hostInfoTable
hostInfoTable.description: A list of Switch Configuration Host Entries

hostInfoEntry.name: hostInfoEntry
hostInfoEntry.description: A list of Host properties for the Switch

hostInfoIndex.name: hostInfoIndex
hostInfoIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the Switch Host Info Table.

hostInfoName.name: hostInfoName
hostInfoName.description: The name of this Switch Host Entry.

hostInfoIp.name: hostInfoIp
hostInfoIp.description: The IP Address for the host.

hostInfoComm.name: hostInfoComm
hostInfoComm.description: The name of the community this host belongs to.

serialBaudRate.name: serialBaudRate
serialBaudRate.description: The baud rate in bits per second of the RS-232 port.

modemControlLines.name: modemControlLines
modemControlLines.description: Indicates whether the RS-232 port modem control lines are enabled.

spanOnOff.name: spanOnOff
spanOnOff.description: Turns Spanning Tree ON/OFF for the switch.

spanResetDefaults.name: spanResetDefaults
spanResetDefaults.description: Reset all settable spanning tree parameters to defaults.

spanRapid.name: spanRapid
spanRapid.description: When spanType is STP, turns Spanning Tree Rapid Reconfiguration ON/OFF.

spanPortTable.name: spanPortTable
spanPortTable.description: Table containing per-port status for single spanning tree.

spanPortEntry.name: spanPortEntry
spanPortEntry.description: Per-port status for single spanning tree.

spanPortPort.name: spanPortPort
spanPortPort.description: The port number on the switch.

spanPortQuickStatus.name: spanPortQuickStatus
spanPortQuickStatus.description: The current status, enabled or disabled, of Port Quick for this port.

spanPortAuto.name: spanPortAuto
spanPortAuto.description: Path cost is either Fixed or Auto. If Auto, cost is calculated automatically, and depends on media data rates and link aggregation.

fanNumFans.name: fanNumFans
fanNumFans.description: The total number of fans possible in this chassis. A fan need not be present to count.

fanInfoEntry.name: fanInfoEntry
fanInfoEntry.description: A list of Fan properties for the Switch

fanIndex.name: fanIndex
fanIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the Switch Fan Table.

psNumber.name: psNumber
psNumber.description: The number of power supplies this chassis is capable of holding. A power supply need not be present to count.

psInfoTable.name: psInfoTable
psInfoTable.description: A list of Power Supply States

psInfoEntry.name: psInfoEntry
psInfoEntry.description: A list of Power Supply properties for the Switch

psIndex.name: psIndex
psIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the Switch Power Supply Table.

psStatus.name: psStatus
psStatus.description: States operational status of Power Supply.

tempCurrent.name: tempCurrent
tempCurrent.description: The current temperature of the switch in degrees centigrade.

tempAlarm.name: tempAlarm
tempAlarm.description: The status of the temperature alarm. This alarm is on if the current temperature exceeds the high water mark.

tempHighest.name: tempHighest
tempHighest.description: The highest temperature reached after the temperature alarm. If the alarm is not active, the value is zero.

tempHigh.name: tempHigh
tempHigh.description: The high water mark for the temperature. If this temperature is exceeded, the temperature alarm is activated.

tempLow.name: tempLow
tempLow.description: The low water mark for the temperature. If the temperature falls below the low water mark, the temperature alarm will be reset.

gigabitPortTable.name: gigabitPortTable
gigabitPortTable.description: This table contains the per port gigabit configurables. The indexes reference a gigabit slot, and the ports numbered from one from the left most port.

gigabitPortTableEntry.name: gigabitPortTableEntry
gigabitPortTableEntry.description: A list of gigabit configurables for the switch

gigabitPortTableSlot.name: gigabitPortTableSlot
gigabitPortTableSlot.description: The slot in which this gigabit card resides. This slot should be the same as one of the valid gigabit slots in the slot table of this MIB.

gigabitPortTablePort.name: gigabitPortTablePort
gigabitPortTablePort.description: The number of the gigabit port on the card. These ports specify an individual port on a gigabit switch or a gigabit repeater. A port here does not represent a unique interface in the interfaces table.

gigabitPortTableLinkState.name: gigabitPortTableLinkState
gigabitPortTableLinkState.description: This field shows the current link state of the gigabit sub-port.

gigabitPortTablePortAutoNeg.name: gigabitPortTablePortAutoNeg
gigabitPortTablePortAutoNeg.description: The current ability of this port to participate in autonegotiation.

tenHundredPortTable.name: tenHundredPortTable
tenHundredPortTable.description: This table contains the per port information for the 10/100 Ethernet boards in the system. This table will be indexed by slot and port.

tenHundredPortTableEntry.name: tenHundredPortTableEntry
tenHundredPortTableEntry.description: A list of 10/100 Ethernet configurables for the switch.

tenHundredPortTableSlot.name: tenHundredPortTableSlot
tenHundredPortTableSlot.description: The slot in which this 10/100 card resides. This slot should be the same as one of the valid 10/100 slots in the slot table of this MIB.

tenHundredPortTablePort.name: tenHundredPortTablePort
tenHundredPortTablePort.description: The number of the 10/100 port on the system. A port here represents a unique interface in the the interfaces table.

tenHundredPortTableLinkState.name: tenHundredPortTableLinkState
tenHundredPortTableLinkState.description: This field shows the current link state of the 10/100 port.

tenHundredPortTableConfig.name: tenHundredPortTableConfig
tenHundredPortTableConfig.description: The autonegotiate mode, speed, and duplex mode for this port. If link state is UP, then this object represents the settings for the active connect. If link state is DOWN, then this ojbect represents the connection mode(s) that this port will accept.

vlanValid.name: vlanValid
vlanValid.description: This field displays if the current VLAN configuration in the Switch is valid.

vlanConfigTable.name: vlanConfigTable
vlanConfigTable.description: This table contains the virtual lan configuration parameters for each virtual lan configured in the system.

vlanConfigEntry.name: vlanConfigEntry
vlanConfigEntry.description: An entry containing information about the Virtual Lan configuration.

vlanConfigName.name: vlanConfigName
vlanConfigName.description: The name associated with this virtual lan ID.

vlanConfigIpAddr.name: vlanConfigIpAddr
vlanConfigIpAddr.description: The IP address associated with this virtual lan.

vlanConfigNetmask.name: vlanConfigNetmask
vlanConfigNetmask.description: The netmask associated with this virtual lan.

vlanConfigBroadcast.name: vlanConfigBroadcast
vlanConfigBroadcast.description: The broadcast address associated with this virtual lan.

vlanConfigRouting.name: vlanConfigRouting
vlanConfigRouting.description: Enable or disable routing on a per-vlan basis.

vlanReset.name: vlanReset
vlanReset.description: Reset VLAN configuration to factory defaults.

vlanPortTable.name: vlanPortTable
vlanPortTable.description: This table contains the virtual lan configuration parameters which are configured on a per-port basis.

vlanPortEntry.name: vlanPortEntry
vlanPortEntry.description: An entry containing the virtual lan configuration parameters which are configured on a per-port basis.

vlanPortNumber.name: vlanPortNumber
vlanPortNumber.description: External port number. This number corresponds to the ifTable ifIndex.

vlanPortTrustedVid.name: vlanPortTrustedVid
vlanPortTrustedVid.description: If VlanPortTrustedVid is 'true', then the VID of tagged frames is alwasy used, otherwise, the PVID of the port is used even if the frame is tagged.

vlanPortTrustedPriority.name: vlanPortTrustedPriority
vlanPortTrustedPriority.description: If VlanPortTrustedPriority is 'true', then the priority of tagged frames is always used, otherwise, the default port priority is used even if the frame is tagged.

routingRouterId.name: routingRouterId
routingRouterId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the switch. By convention, to ensure uniqueness, this should default to the value of one of the router's IP interface addresses. This object cannot be accessed unless GateD is enabled.

routingScanInterval.name: routingScanInterval
routingScanInterval.description: The number of seconds indicating how often GateD will check with the kernel for the interface changes when no notification is received from the kernel. This object cannot be accessed unless routing is enabled.

routingEnable.name: routingEnable
routingEnable.description: Enable/disable routing. Writing enableInit to this object starts the GateD process, but does not enable any routing protocols. enableRestore starts the GateD process and restores the GateD configuration from nonvolatile memory. When read, this object will return either enabled or disabled.

routingOspfPref.name: routingOspfPref
routingOspfPref.description: The preference level for OSPF-based routing This object cannot be accessed unless routing is enabled.

routingStaticConfigPref.name: routingStaticConfigPref
routingStaticConfigPref.description: The preference level for the default static route. This object cannot be accessed unless routing is enabled.

routingRipPref.name: routingRipPref
routingRipPref.description: The preference level for rip-based routing This object cannot be accessed unless routing is enabled.

routingOspfAsExtPref.name: routingOspfAsExtPref
routingOspfAsExtPref.description: The preference level for OSPF as extern based routing This object cannot be accessed unless routing is enabled.

routingIfPrefTable.name: routingIfPrefTable
routingIfPrefTable.description: A list of local interfaces and their preference levels.

routingIfPrefAddress.name: routingIfPrefAddress
routingIfPrefAddress.description: The IP Address of this system on the indicated subnet. For unnumbered interfaces, the value 0.0.0.N, where the least significant 24 bits (N) is the ifIndex for the IP Interface in network byte order.

routingIfPref.name: routingIfPref
routingIfPref.description: The preference level for this interface

staticRouteNumber.name: staticRouteNumber
staticRouteNumber.description: The number of current staticRouteTable entries that are not invalid.

staticRouteTable.name: staticRouteTable
staticRouteTable.description: This entity's static IP routing config table.

staticRouteEntry.name: staticRouteEntry
staticRouteEntry.description: A particular static route to a particular destination.

staticRouteDest.name: staticRouteDest
staticRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. This object may not take a Multicast (Class D) address value. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the staticRouteMask object is not equal to x.

staticRouteMask.name: staticRouteMask
staticRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the staticRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the staticRouteMask by reference to the IP Address Class. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the staticRouteDest object is not equal to staticRouteDest.

staticRouteNextHop.name: staticRouteNextHop
staticRouteNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next sys- tem en route; Otherwise, 0.0.0.0.

staticRouteIf.name: staticRouteIf
staticRouteIf.description: The local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached.

staticRoutePref.name: staticRoutePref
staticRoutePref.description: The preference value for this route. Default value is 20 for the default route, 60 otherwise.

staticRouteStatus.name: staticRouteStatus
staticRouteStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

routingSaveConfig.name: routingSaveConfig
routingSaveConfig.description: Write to this object to save the current router configuration to nonvolatile storage. The agent will perform an activate before saving. You cannot save the configuration unless routing is enabled.

errorTable.name: errorTable
errorTable.description: A list of SNMP User-error Entries.

errorEntry.name: errorEntry
errorEntry.description: A description of an SNMP user-error.

errorIndex.name: errorIndex
errorIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the Error Table.

errorMsg.name: errorMsg
errorMsg.description: The description of the SNMP configuration error.

errorOid.name: errorOid
errorOid.description: The object ID for the SNMP manager request which caused this error.

errorTime.name: errorTime
errorTime.description: The time, in hundreths of a second since system boot, that the error occurred.

clearErrorTable.name: clearErrorTable
clearErrorTable.description: Writing true to this object clears the SNMP Error Table.

linkStateTable.name: linkStateTable
linkStateTable.description: This table contains the link states of every port on the switch, indexed by slot number and local (per-slot) port number.

linkStateEntry.name: linkStateEntry
linkStateEntry.description: Each entry contains the link state and last-changed time of a port on the switch, indexed by slot number and local port number.

linkStateSlot.name: linkStateSlot
linkStateSlot.description: The index of this media card on the Switch chassis. Media card indices begin at one, at the top of the chassis.

linkStatePort.name: linkStatePort
linkStatePort.description: The index of this port on the media card. Port indices begin at one, at the left side of the card, when viewed from the front.

linkStateState.name: linkStateState
linkStateState.description: The current link state of this port.

linkStateTime.name: linkStateTime
linkStateTime.description: The most recent time, in hundreths of a second since system boot, that this port's link state changed.

carrierCPSlotID.name: carrierCPSlotID
carrierCPSlotID.description: Indicates which slot contains the master CP.

carrierStatusA.name: carrierStatusA
carrierStatusA.description: Indicates whether CP board A is inserted, and if inserted, whether it is running.

carrierStatusB.name: carrierStatusB
carrierStatusB.description: Indicates whether CP board B is inserted, and if inserted, whether it is running.

moduleTable.name: moduleTable
moduleTable.description: Table containing hardware and software configuration information.

moduleSlotNum.name: moduleSlotNum
moduleSlotNum.description: The Slot ID of the switch. Slot 1 is physically the top slot in a chassis.

moduleCard.name: moduleCard
moduleCard.description: The specific card within a slot.

moduleDataValid.name: moduleDataValid
moduleDataValid.description: Indicates whether the version text is initialized.

moduleText.name: moduleText
moduleText.description: A text string containing hardware or sofware version information.

pingHostAddress.name: pingHostAddress
pingHostAddress.description: The hostname or host IP address for the PING.

pingRequest.name: pingRequest
pingRequest.description: Writing any value to this object sends a PING.

pingStatus.name: pingStatus
pingStatus.description: Status of most recent ping request.

dnsEnable.name: dnsEnable
dnsEnable.description: The current state of the Domain Name Server in the Switch. If this field is set to enable, Domain Name Services will be supported.

dnsDomainName.name: dnsDomainName
dnsDomainName.description: The Domain Name for the network this switch is on.

dnsPrimaryServer.name: dnsPrimaryServer
dnsPrimaryServer.description: The primary DNS server for the network this switch is on.

dnsBackupServer.name: dnsBackupServer
dnsBackupServer.description: The secondary DNS server for the network this switch is on.

stormBcastControlTable.name: stormBcastControlTable
stormBcastControlTable.description: Table containing configuration and status information for broadcast storm control.

stormBcastControlEntry.name: stormBcastControlEntry
stormBcastControlEntry.description: Configuration and status for broadcast storm control.

stormBcastControlPort.name: stormBcastControlPort
stormBcastControlPort.description: The port number on the switch, equivalent to ifIndex.

stormBcastControlThreshold.name: stormBcastControlThreshold
stormBcastControlThreshold.description: The broadcast frame rate, in percent of total bandwidth, at which discarding is triggered for this port.

stormBcastControlDiscardPeriod.name: stormBcastControlDiscardPeriod
stormBcastControlDiscardPeriod.description: The amount of time, in seconds, that discarding will continue on this port once triggered. If the discard period is set to zero seconds and the port transitions to discarding state, then user intervention is required to remove the port from discarding state.

stormBcastControlRate.name: stormBcastControlRate
stormBcastControlRate.description: The current broadcast rate, measured as a precentage of total bandwidth, for this port.

stormBcastControlDisables.name: stormBcastControlDisables
stormBcastControlDisables.description: The number of times this port entered the discard state as a result of storm control.

stormBcastControlEnables.name: stormBcastControlEnables
stormBcastControlEnables.description: The number of times this port exited the discard state as a result of storm control.

stormBcastControlTimeLeft.name: stormBcastControlTimeLeft
stormBcastControlTimeLeft.description: The number of seconds remaining until this port will exit the discard state.

stormBcastControlStatus.name: stormBcastControlStatus
stormBcastControlStatus.description: The current status of this port with respect to storm control. If the port is in the discarding state, then writing 'exitDiscardState' to stormBcastControlStatus will cause the port to exit the discarding state. No other value may be written to this object.

stormMcastControlTable.name: stormMcastControlTable
stormMcastControlTable.description: Table containing configuration and status information for multicast storm control.

stormMcastControlEntry.name: stormMcastControlEntry
stormMcastControlEntry.description: Configuration and status for multicast storm control.

stormMcastControlPort.name: stormMcastControlPort
stormMcastControlPort.description: The port number on the switch, equivalent to ifIndex.

stormMcastControlThreshold.name: stormMcastControlThreshold
stormMcastControlThreshold.description: The multicast frame rate, in percent of total bandwidth, at which discarding is triggered for this port.

stormMcastControlDiscardPeriod.name: stormMcastControlDiscardPeriod
stormMcastControlDiscardPeriod.description: The amount of time, in seconds, that discarding will continue on this port once triggered. If the discard period is set to zero seconds and the port transitions to discarding state, then user intervention is required to remove the port from discarding state.

stormMcastControlRate.name: stormMcastControlRate
stormMcastControlRate.description: The current multicast rate, measured as a precentage of total bandwidth, for this port.

stormMcastControlDisables.name: stormMcastControlDisables
stormMcastControlDisables.description: The number of times this port entered the discard state as a result of storm control.

stormMcastControlEnables.name: stormMcastControlEnables
stormMcastControlEnables.description: The number of times this port exited the discard state as a result of storm control.

stormMcastControlTimeLeft.name: stormMcastControlTimeLeft
stormMcastControlTimeLeft.description: The number of seconds remaining until this port will exit the discard state.

stormMcastControlStatus.name: stormMcastControlStatus
stormMcastControlStatus.description: The current status of this port with respect to storm control. If the port is in the discarding state, then writing 'exitDiscardState' to stormMcastControlStatus will cause the port to exit the discarding state. No other value may be written to this object.

igmpSnoopingEnable.name: igmpSnoopingEnable
igmpSnoopingEnable.description: Enable or disable IGMP snooping for system.

igmpSnoopingResetControl.name: igmpSnoopingResetControl
igmpSnoopingResetControl.description: Reset all control ports in the system to NORMAL mode. Reading always returns other(1), Writing reset(2) performs the reset.

igmpSnoopingResetData.name: igmpSnoopingResetData
igmpSnoopingResetData.description: Reset all data ports in the system to NORMAL mode. Reading always returns other(1), Writing reset(2) performs the reset.

igmpSnoopingVlanResetData.name: igmpSnoopingVlanResetData
igmpSnoopingVlanResetData.description: Reset all data ports in the vlan to NORMAL mode. Reading always returns other(1), Writing reset(2) performs the reset.

igmpSnoopingVlanResetControl.name: igmpSnoopingVlanResetControl
igmpSnoopingVlanResetControl.description: Reset all control ports in the vlan to NORMAL mode. Reading always returns other(1), Writing reset(2) performs the reset.

igmpSnoopingDataPortNumber.name: igmpSnoopingDataPortNumber
igmpSnoopingDataPortNumber.description: External port number. This number corresponds to the ifTable ifIndex.

igmpSnoopingDataPortGroup.name: igmpSnoopingDataPortGroup
igmpSnoopingDataPortGroup.description: All --all multicast forbidden or forwarded Ip --specified ip forbidden or forwarded

igmpSnoopingDataPortIpAddr.name: igmpSnoopingDataPortIpAddr
igmpSnoopingDataPortIpAddr.description: Multicast IP Address fixed or forbidden, if data port group ip=2

igmpSnoopingDataPortState.name: igmpSnoopingDataPortState
igmpSnoopingDataPortState.description: Normal --default value. Fixed --Permanent group assignement Forbid --Never in the defined group assignment. Write fixed(4) or forbid(5) to this object to create a new row or modify an existing row. Write normal(3) to this object to remove an existing row.

igmpSnoopingControlPortNumber.name: igmpSnoopingControlPortNumber
igmpSnoopingControlPortNumber.description: External port number. This number corresponds to the ifTable ifIndex.

igmpSnoopingControlPortState.name: igmpSnoopingControlPortState
igmpSnoopingControlPortState.description: Normal --control port based on protocol snooping Fixed --always a control port Forbid --never a control port.

igmpSnoopingControlPortRowStatus.name: igmpSnoopingControlPortRowStatus
igmpSnoopingControlPortRowStatus.description: Used to control creation and deletion of rows.

igmpSnoopingStatusTable.name: igmpSnoopingStatusTable
igmpSnoopingStatusTable.description: Table of entries for reporting IGMP snooping status with Mac address to Port address mapping

igmpSnoopingPort.name: igmpSnoopingPort
igmpSnoopingPort.description: External port number. This number corresponds to the ifTable ifIndex.

igmpSnoopingIpStatusTable.name: igmpSnoopingIpStatusTable
igmpSnoopingIpStatusTable.description: Table of entries for reporting IGMP snooping status with Mac address to Ip address mapping

igmpSnoopingIpAddress.name: igmpSnoopingIpAddress
igmpSnoopingIpAddress.description: Multicast IP address. There can be several of these for each multicast mac address.

pvstpTable.name: pvstpTable
pvstpTable.description: Per Vlan Spanning Tree Protocol Table.

pvstpEntry.name: pvstpEntry
pvstpEntry.description: Information about an instance of a spanning tree for the specified vlan. All time (TimeTic, Timeout) values are in hundreths of a second.

pvstpProtocolSpecification.name: pvstpProtocolSpecification
pvstpProtocolSpecification.description: What spanning tree protocol is being run. ieee8021w1s1 indicates the version 1.0 implementation of 802.1w and 802.1s.

pvstpPriority.name: pvstpPriority
pvstpPriority.description: The first 2 octets of the bridge identifier.

pvstpDesignatedRoot.name: pvstpDesignatedRoot
pvstpDesignatedRoot.description: The current root of the spanning tree.

pvstpHoldTime.name: pvstpHoldTime
pvstpHoldTime.description: Minimum interval between transmition of configuration messages.

pvstpForwardDelay.name: pvstpForwardDelay
pvstpForwardDelay.description: Length of time spent in each state.

pvstpBridgeMaxAge.name: pvstpBridgeMaxAge
pvstpBridgeMaxAge.description: Value in hundredths of seconds which all bridges use for max age when this bridge is a root. Actual resolution is one second.

pvstpBridgeHelloTime.name: pvstpBridgeHelloTime
pvstpBridgeHelloTime.description: Value to used for hello time when this bridge is a root.

pvstpBridgeForwardDelay.name: pvstpBridgeForwardDelay
pvstpBridgeForwardDelay.description: Value used for forward delay when this bridge is a root.

pvstpBridgeRapid.name: pvstpBridgeRapid
pvstpBridgeRapid.description: When spanType is pvstp, turns Spanning Tree Rapid Reconfiguration ON/OFF for the vlan.

pvstpBridgeId.name: pvstpBridgeId
pvstpBridgeId.description: The Bridge ID in use for this VLAN.

pvstpPortTable.name: pvstpPortTable
pvstpPortTable.description: Per Vlan Spanning Tree Protocol Port Table.

pvstpPortEntry.name: pvstpPortEntry
pvstpPortEntry.description: Information about a specific port for an instance of a spanning tree for the specified vlan. All time (TimeTic, Timeout) values are in hundreths of a second.

pvstpPort.name: pvstpPort
pvstpPort.description: External port number. This number corresponds to the ifTable ifIndex.

pvstpPortPriority.name: pvstpPortPriority
pvstpPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field.

pvstpPortState.name: pvstpPortState
pvstpPortState.description: The port state defined by the application of the spanning tree protocol.

pvstpPortEnable.name: pvstpPortEnable
pvstpPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

pvstpPortPathCost.name: pvstpPortPathCost
pvstpPortPathCost.description: The contribution of the port to the path cost. Actual cost ranges from 1 to 65535. Zero is a magic number which sets the cost automatically.

pvstpPortDesignatedRoot.name: pvstpPortDesignatedRoot
pvstpPortDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the current root, as transmitted by the current designated bridge for the segment.

pvstpPortDesignatedCost.name: pvstpPortDesignatedCost
pvstpPortDesignatedCost.description: Path cost for the designated port.

pvstpPortDesignatedBridge.name: pvstpPortDesignatedBridge
pvstpPortDesignatedBridge.description: Bridge identifier of the bridge which this port see as the designated bridge for the segment.

pvstpPortDesignatedPort.name: pvstpPortDesignatedPort
pvstpPortDesignatedPort.description: Port identifer of the port on the designated bridge for the segment.

pvstpPortForwardTransitions.name: pvstpPortForwardTransitions
pvstpPortForwardTransitions.description: The number of times the port has transitioned from learning to forwarding state.

pvstpPortQuick.name: pvstpPortQuick
pvstpPortQuick.description: When spanType is pvstp, turns quick port reconfiguration ON/OFF for the port.

pvstpPortAuto.name: pvstpPortAuto
pvstpPortAuto.description: Path cost is either Fixed or Auto. If Auto, cost is calculated automatically, and depends on media data rates and link aggregation.

relayEnable.name: relayEnable
relayEnable.description: Enabled-disabled status of BOOTP/DHCP relay agent.

relayMaxHops.name: relayMaxHops
relayMaxHops.description: Number of hops for the discard threshold for the BOOTP/DHCP relay agent.

relayServerEntry.name: relayServerEntry
relayServerEntry.description: Each BOOTP/DHCP server entry consists of a server index and an IP address.

relayServerIndex.name: relayServerIndex
relayServerIndex.description: Index of a BOOTP/DHCP relay server IP address.

relayServerAddress.name: relayServerAddress
relayServerAddress.description: IP address of a BOOTP/DHCP relay server.

portMirrorEntry.name: portMirrorEntry
portMirrorEntry.description: Information which defines which ports are currently being mirrored.

portMirrorSourcePort.name: portMirrorSourcePort
portMirrorSourcePort.description: Port number of port being mirrored.

portMirrorMonitorPort.name: portMirrorMonitorPort
portMirrorMonitorPort.description: Port number of the monitor port.

portMirrorRowStatus.name: portMirrorRowStatus
portMirrorRowStatus.description: Used to control creation and deletion of rows.

ipAccessCtlEntry.name: ipAccessCtlEntry
ipAccessCtlEntry.description: Information which defines the rules for IP Access Control.

ipAccessCtlEnable.name: ipAccessCtlEnable
ipAccessCtlEnable.description: Enabled-disabled status of IP Access Control.

fdbLearningMode.name: fdbLearningMode
fdbLearningMode.description: FDB learning mode; either Independent VLAN Learning(IVL), or Shared VLAN Learning(SVL).

fdbAgeId.name: fdbAgeId
fdbAgeId.description: FDB ID for this entry. In IVL mode, this object is equivalent to the VLAN ID. In SVL mode, this object is one for all entries.

fdbAgeStatus.name: fdbAgeStatus
fdbAgeStatus.description: Enable(1) or disable(2) aging. In SVL Mode, this object controls aging for the entire FDB. In IVL Mode, this object controls aging on a per-VLAN basis.

fdbAgeTime.name: fdbAgeTime
fdbAgeTime.description: Aging time for layer-2 entries. In SVL Mode, this object controls aging for the entire FDB. In IVL Mode, this object controls aging on a per-VLAN basis.

carrierCPSlotChangeEvent.name: carrierCPSlotChangeEvent
carrierCPSlotChangeEvent.description: The master CP board has changed from slotA to slotB or vice-versa.

carrierStatusAChangeEvent.name: carrierStatusAChangeEvent
carrierStatusAChangeEvent.description: The status (inserted/running) of the CP in slot A has changed.

carrierStatusBChangeEvent.name: carrierStatusBChangeEvent
carrierStatusBChangeEvent.description: The status (inserted/running) of the CP in slot B has changed.

mediaCardChangeEvent.name: mediaCardChangeEvent
mediaCardChangeEvent.description: One or more of the media cards has been inserted or removed.

fanFailEvent.name: fanFailEvent
fanFailEvent.description: One or more the fans has failed.

powerSupplyFailEvent.name: powerSupplyFailEvent
powerSupplyFailEvent.description: One or more of the power supplies has failed.

highTemperatureEvent.name: highTemperatureEvent
highTemperatureEvent.description: The temperature has exceeded the high temperature mark; the switch is shutting down immediately.

risingTemperatureEvent.name: risingTemperatureEvent
risingTemperatureEvent.description: The temperature of the switch is rising. If the temperature continues to rise, the switch will shut down.

fallingTemperatureEvent.name: fallingTemperatureEvent
fallingTemperatureEvent.description: The temperature of the switch was dangerously high, but now the temperature has fallen back into the normal operating range.

stormBcastControlDiscardEvent.name: stormBcastControlDiscardEvent
stormBcastControlDiscardEvent.description: The broadcast framerate on this port has exceeded the threshold level set by the user. The storm control software has put this port into frame discard mode.

stormMcastControlDiscardEvent.name: stormMcastControlDiscardEvent
stormMcastControlDiscardEvent.description: The multicast framerate on this port has exceeded the threshold level set by the user. The storm control software has put this port into frame discard mode.
